&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The fourth chapter of Bhagwat Gita is Jnyana (Knowledge) Yoga. It has 42 slokas. What is the meaning of Jnyana or Knowledge in the context of Bhagwat Gita and Hindu Scriptures? What is the power of Knowledge? What is the role of this in Liberating person from suffering? These are the ideas dicussed here.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
